flowRoot.flowPara: I don't think these work at all. The icons put extra cognitive burden on the user to differentiate between the types of results, the extra step is a barrier to get to the result. I would much rather have Maps do the first decision on what kind of result gets the preference.
Maps should present what it thinks is the most relevant result and we should provide a mean to correct it if we're wrong. I'm sure somebody took notes from GUADEC on this.
The result view pops up as soon as an autocompleted entry is found.
Search should autocomplete for address book contacts and places.
There should be some hurestics for ordering based on importance.
Note: Autocompleting against places might not be technically possible right now.
The two buttons are for changing map type.
The three buttons below are for showing extra data overlaid on the map.
* Transit shows public transportation coverage in the area.
This pops up the routing sidebar.
Marker will always be visible on the two innermost zoom levels.
Pressing the marker shows the bubble. Clicking again outside or the escape key will hide the bubble again.
If we are able to find a picture of the place (on for example wikipedia), use that, otherwise a general icon for the type of POI
Behaves just like the Point of Interest above, but these addresses are being fetched from your address book.
If the contact has a profile picture, use that, otherwise a general contact icon.
On search results, the bubble will be immediatley visible.
Clicking outside it will hide the bubble and just show the marker. Making a new search will hade the marker.
If we are able to find a picture of the place (on for example wikipedia), use that, otherwise a general marker icon.
Current location only has accuracy information. Apart from that it behaves just like the Point of Interest bubble.
It's icon is the current location icon.
Behaves just like the Contact, but shows the last checkins for your contacts. Only shows checkins that are more recent than 3 hours ago.
